\par
SATA Connectors: Usually positioned on the edge of the motherboard, these connectors are often oriented horizontally and may be grouped together. They are used for connecting storage devices like SSDs and HDDs.\par
\par
PCI-E Slot (Peripheral Component Interconnect Express): These slots are typically found toward the bottom of the motherboard. They are longer and are used for expansion cards like graphics cards and network cards.\par
